<TEXTAREA NAME="ReplyMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">[QUOTE]Originally posted by kaharz:
[B]Thanks for stepping up and saying something Rayne.  It is a crappy way to go about things but it is the only way really.

Untill a bit ago I didn't even think of getting the epic (small guild and not enough time on line to do the quest or generate enough friends to take down the quest NPCs)
Now I am in a guild strong enough to help me with the more difficult NPCs, but I doubt I will start the quest the anytime soon.  I'm generally an average player.  Most days I only get a few hours in, but that is mainly by choice, and I've spent countless hours on camps before, but after almost 2 years the game just isn't as entertaining and my social life has come out of it's coma and now only needs oxygen tubes to keep it alive.  So my EQ time is a bit limited.  ... going off topic, just wanted to make the point I'm not a "hardcore" gamer and am becoming more so the casual gamer.
The epic would be nice, but I don't need it. There are plenty of other clerics on my server with it.  True only one of the three 50+ clerics in my guild (hopefully I will eventually be in that group) has it, and he isn't on a whole lot, but raids managed before without it.  I must say it's nice after your inexperienced PoS raid spawns Sirran before killing all the other faeries and then procceeds to pull another faerie past him (glad I went LD right before it happened, although I doubt I would have had time to heal anyone and get agged myself), having a cleric around with the epic is very convient, but not vital.  It is not like trying to take an insanely MR mob without any tanks.

Don't get me wrong I would love to have the epic, but I don't want to spend the time or deal with the frustration.  I already went through enough with the Aegis of Life, and I had nothing better to do at the time.

I think Verrant really screwed up on this quest.  It's true that the elevated demand creates a bigger problem at the bottlenecks. But that is the same as saying, the reason traffic is so bad is because there are to many cars.  I understand Verrant wants to control the influx of epic items into the game, but causing a backlog is not the way to do it.  The rest of the quest should take more time, and be of a greater difficulty to accomplish.  Did they really think there would not be a high demand for this epic?  It directly benefits large numbers of people at once.  Many of the epics do not directly benefit anyone but the owner.  Of course all the epics do have a benefit to everyone fighting with the owner in some way, but it is not a direct or obvious benefit.  I am not at all happy with the way this quest is designed, so I choose not to do it unless I have absolutely nothing better, and a really bad case of insomnia.  If I was a mage, I doubt I would do that quest either because of the pegasus cloak malarkey.  Either way, this is running long, I'm sure it's getting incoherent, so I'm going to go to bed.

Once again though.. thanks Rayne, someone had to step up to flamethrower.

Kaharz Stronginthearm
48th lvl cleric of Brell
Rodcet Nife
Troubles Band[/B][/QUOTE]

</TEXTAREA>
